<subSubSection id="06F0C8AE6CF8660D027148AC06F0412C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="9D72125DD49EC7F2DC07E75580911B3C" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7D543E33F132BB8DE0BC788DAAB64C9" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
A combination of the Latin words: &quot; 
<emphasis id="3229952E661870DF37698FC132DCC94C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">platys</emphasis>
&quot; + &quot; 
<emphasis id="A4FC4749DE7401B2F00DE9FBC9F09CBF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">rhinos</emphasis>
&quot;, referring to the flat carina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
